What You Should Know: – Cohere Health®, a leader in clinical intelligence solutions tailored for health plans and risk-bearing providers raises $90M in a Series C funding round led by Temasek, with continued strong support from existing investors including Deerfield Management, Define Ventures, Flare Capital Partners, Longitude Capital, and Polaris Partners. This latest round brings Cohere Health’s total funding to an impressive $200M. – The infusion of new capital is earmarked to propel Cohere Health into its next phase of growth. Key initiatives include scaling its flagship Cohere Unify™ platform, expanding its application into new clinical use cases, and significantly deepening investment in its portfolio of AI-powered products. Modernizing Healthcare Collaboration with Cohere Unify™ Cohere Unify™ is at the heart of the company’s mission, designed to establish critical points of collaboration between health plans and healthcare providers. The platform aims to modernize the often-cumbersome utilization management (UM) process by personalizing provider workflows and optimizing engagement through the use of real-time performance data. By streamlining these interactions, Cohere Health is laying the groundwork for a broader transformation in clinical decision-making. The platform has demonstrated measurable administrative and clinical efficiencies, effectively  ...    accelerates patients’ time to care, and ultimately contributes to improved outcomes for health plan members. A standout feature of Cohere’s precision clinical insights is the ability for up to 90% of service requests to be auto-approved,  ...    Cohere Health emphasizes its clinician-led model and a “responsible AI-first” approach. This philosophy ensures that clinical expertise remains central to every solution the company develops, underpinning Cohere’s commitment to  ...    healthcare processes. Significant Growth and Industry Recognition Over the past year, Cohere Health has achieved notable mileston